+### 1.4 Notes on IonQ and Fusion-QEC
+Note: IonQ uses **Clifford Noise Reduction (CliNR)** for trapped-ion QEC, achieving ~2x logical error reduction with 3:1 qubit and 2:1 gate overhead.  
+IonQ integrates **photonic interconnects** for scaling/networking but does **not** use fusion-based QEC.  
+Fusion-QEC described here refers to photonic architectures (e.g. PsiQuantum, Xanadu), leveraging fusion gates on entangled resource states.

